  <discussion>Ptychostomum pseudotriquetrum is one of the most common and widespread species of Bryaceae, absent only from the subtropics, tropics, and central Pacific Islands. Ovate decurrent leaves, short, stout awn, dense areolation, dioicous sexual condition, and long radiculose stems are characteristic. Ptychostomum bimum is smaller, with much weaker decurrencies, and is synoicous.</discussion>
